    "text": "<@UJ6LDMMN0> I also saw the causal tree page too – thank you! Something I’ve not seen with causal trees is how to create stable revision semantics. It’s wonderful for eventual consistency, but I don’t see how to create types in it where I can identify a specific system state and pass that about being sure that everyone will be able to resolve exactly the same configuration that I have identified. I could also hash what I see, but then the state might have changed since the hash was created and surely there needs to be a way to avoid this.",
